Q: What is SQL NOT NULL constraint?
NOT NULL constraint is used to ensure that the value in the filed cannot be a NULL
 (AGE &gt; 18), PRIMARY KEY (EmpID));

Q: Write an SQL Query to select all records from the table?
Select * from table_name;
Select * from table_name;
.

Q: How to get each name only once from an employee table?
By using the DISTINCT keyword, we could get each name only once,
SELECT DISTINCT employee_name FROM employee_table;
SELECT DISTINCT employee_name FROM employee_table;
.

Q: How to rename a column in the output of SQL query?
By using SQL AS keyword
 SELECT column_name AS new_name FROM table_name;
 SELECT column_name AS new_name FROM table_name;
.
